Problem:
class EnvironmentMonitor {
    private int temperature;
    private boolean airConditioningOn;

    public EnvironmentMonitor(int temp) {
        temperature = temp;
        airConditioningOn = false;
    }

    public void adjustTemperature() {
        if (temperature > 25) {
            airConditioningOn = true;
            temperature -= 5;
        } else if (temperature < 18) {
            airConditioningOn = false;
            temperature += 3;
        }
    }

    public int getTemperature() {
        return temperature;
    }

    public boolean isAirConditioningOn() {
        return airConditioningOn;
    }
}",

If we set the initial temperature to 26 degrees, will the air conditioning turn on after calling adjustTemperature()?
